The recent activity involved opening PR #13, which includes atomic session rotation, invariant wiring, and HTTP-layer conformance tests. This PR addresses several issues identified during a deep code review.

*   A new test, `TestToken_RefreshInvalidatesOldToken`, was added to `internal/oidcapi/refresh_rotation_test.go` to specifically isolate the invalidation signal without affecting successor tokens or asserting family revocation. This test is tagged with `//harbor:invariant INV-REFRESH-ROTATION-INVALIDATES-OLD` and is now listed in `invariants/registry.yaml` as enforced by the `intern...` component. `run_mrhe59j9q7kx`
*   A fix for a non-atomic rotation gap was implemented by introducing a single-transaction revoke+create in `DBSessionStore`. This is achieved through the `RotateSession` method in `internal/oidc/refresh.go`, which is atomically implemented in `InMemorySessionStore` and uses a pgx transaction in `DBSessionStore`. `run_mrhe1hakdthj`
*   Deep review fixes, including distinguishing `pgx.ErrNoRows` from other DB errors in `GetSessionByTokenHash` and handling `ExpiresAt.Valid == false` (NULL expiry) by failing closed, were addressed and committed. `run_mrhbgq3dshhd`
*   An invariant for `INV-REFRESH-HASH-LOOKUP` was added to verify that tokens are looked up by their SHA-256 hash, not the plaintext, at the store layer. This includes a new test `TestRefreshHashLookup` in `internal/oidc/refresh_test.go` and an entry in `invariants/registry.yaml`. `run_mrhfov1wjh1l`

